        <div class="accordion__item">
            <button class="accordion__btn">

                <span class="accordion__caption"><i class="far fa-lightbulb"></i>How to Donate Unused Medicine?</span>
                <span class="accordion__icon"><i class="fa fa-plus"></i></span>
            </button>

            <div class="accordion__content">
                <p>All donated medication must meet the following criteria:<br>

1)Is unexpired. Some organizations also require the medicine not expire in the near future.<br>
2)Is unopened and in tamper-evident packaging. “Tamper-evident” means the packaging leaves visual evidence once opened (such as a plastic seal). Unit-dose systems, like blister packs, are an example of tamper-evident packaging. Amber vials are not tamper-evident and therefore ineligible for donation.<br>
3)Does not require refrigeration. Some medications require cold storage, such as insulins, injections and eye drops. These are not eligible for donation.<br>
4)Is not a controlled substance. Controlled substances are drugs that are regulated under federal law and can cause physical and mental dependence.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion__item">
            <button class="accordion__btn">

