        <div class="accordion__item">
            <button class="accordion__btn">

                <span class="accordion__caption"><i class="far fa-lightbulb"></i>Are expired medicines truly not usable?</span>
                <span class="accordion__icon"><i class="fa fa-plus"></i></span>
            </button>

            <div class="accordion__content">
                <p>Medicines have expiry dates that indicate the date upto which the manufacturer guarantees their potency and efficacy. “Ongoing research shows that stored under optimal conditions, many drugs retain 90% of their potency for at least five years after the labeled expiration date, and sometimes longer.” says Dan Gikonya.The quality assurance manager of a large pharma company whom I talked to in this regard said that as long as the medicine has not visibly deteriorated, it should be safe to take for at least two years post the expiry date. However, for obvious reasons, expired medicines are inappropriate to donate for human consumption.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

